ProcessEntity.Note:
This component effectively has in 2 different modes of operation:

  1. All Location data is loaded and prepared once for displaying the locations within the map widget
  2. Location data is retreived per request within the specified search radius set up in the configuration

 

Which method is used is down to each implementation. However as a rough rule of thumb for a smaller number of locations > 200, perhaps consider the All in one approach. All possible locations will be avaiable for the user to browse within the map widget. Clicking on Branch list will restrict the list to only those locations available in the currect search radius from the currect location.

 

Option 2 is intended to be for larger data seets e.g 200 plus and restricts the number of locations being loaded into the map widget to only those locations falling within the current search radius of the current location. If the user searchs for another place then the search will trigger another search of the Shared datastore and only those locations which fall within the defined search radius will be applied to the map widget.
